  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering in many countries. Financial institutions, businesses, and professionals in certain industries are typically required to report suspicious transactions or activities to the appropriate authorities. Specific requirements vary by jurisdiction, but generally include:\n\n1. Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n2. Implementation of anti-money laundering (AML) compliance programs\n3. Customer identification and verification procedures\n4. Record-keeping requirements\n5. Training employees to recognize potential money laundering activities\n\nThe exact details and penalties for non-compliance depend on local laws and regulations.",
